This paper deals with image manipulation and generation using deep generative networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to enable users to manipulate natural scenes, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a comprehensive set of qualitative and quantitative results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the approach, which is a common practice in machine learning research (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of graphics and visualization techniques to generate and manipulate images, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper also involves the use of multimedia techniques to manipulate images, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
